  <front>
   <head>A Reasonable Affliction.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="octet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">His Death-Bed poor  lies:</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">His Spouse is in Despair:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With frequent Sobs, and mutual Cries,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">They Both express their Care.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A diff'rent Cause, says Parson ,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The same Effect may give:</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Poor  fears, that He shall Die;</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">His Wife, that He may Live.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
